        <p>
          The center is located at <m>(-3,1)</m>.
          The distance from the center to a vertex is 5 units, hence <m>a=5</m>.
          The minor axis seems to have length 4, so <m>b=2</m>.
          Thus the equation of the ellipse is
          <me>
            \frac{(x+3)^2}{4}+\frac{(y-1)^2}{25} = 1
          </me>.
        </p>
